			<TR>

	 	

		<TD COLSPAN =2 ALIGN = "LEFT" VALIGN = "TOP" WIDTH = 80%>

		<FONT SIZE = 2>
	  
	 	
		<DD><DD>TORONTO, October 9, 1996:  Mackenzie Financial Corporation ("Mackenzie") today announced that as a result of purchases of common shares of Ault Foods Limited ("Ault") by one or more of its mutual fund and private client managed accounts during the month of September, 1996, the aggregate shares of Ault held by all of its managed accounts at the end of September, 1996 was 1,910,700 common shares, representing approximately 10.4% of all outstanding common shares.  Mackenzie specifically disclaims any beneficial ownership of the reported shares, but as investment manager it maintains exclusive power to exercise investment control or direction over such shares for its managed accounts.
	
The shares were acquired in the ordinary course of business, for investment purposes only and not for the purpose of exercising control or direction over Ault.  Mackenzie managed accounts may from time to time acquire additional shares, dispose of some or all of the existing or additional shares or may continue to hold the shares.
	
This press release and the related early warning report are issued in anticipation of the alternative reporting exemption described in the recently proposed OSC Rule respecting early warning reporting.  Neither Mackenzie nor any of its managed accounts presently intend to:<BR><BR><DD>a)  make a formal take-over bid for shares of Ault;<BR><BR><DD>b)  propose a transaction that would constitute a take-over bid in reliance on an exemption in the Securities Act (Ontario); or<BR><BR><DD>c)  propose a reorganization, amalgamation, merger, arrangement or similar business combination with Ault which would result in Mackenzie's managed accounts controlling the company, alone or with others.<BR><BR><DD>   To the best of its knowledge, Mackenzie and its managed accounts do not in the ordinary course of business receive material facts or changes about Ault which have not been publicly disclosed.<BR><BR><DD>   For further information, contact:
					
Harold P. Hands
Executive Vice-President, Legal
Mackenzie Financial Corporation
150 Bloor Street West
Toronto, Ontario
M5S 3B5<BR><BR><DD>Telephone:  (416) 922-5322
 
		 
		</TD>
		


		</TR>

