		<TD COLSPAN =2 ALIGN = "LEFT" VALIGN = "TOP" WIDTH = 80%>

		<FONT SIZE = 2>
	  
	 	
		<DD><DD>Toronto, Ontario - October 31, 1996.<BR><BR><DD>Mackenzie Financial Corporation (TSE & ME - MKF; NASDAQ - MKFCF) reports its unaudited consolidated financial results for the three and six month periods ended September 30, 1996.<BR><BR><DD>THREE MONTH PERIOD:<BR><BR><DD>Revenue for the 3 month period ended 09/30/96 was $84.3 million up 31% from $64.3m reported for the same period last year. Continued growth in Canadian and US-managed mutual fund assets under administration increased management and administration fees by $16.4 million and distribution revenue by $2.7m.<BR><BR><DD>Net earnings increased 30% to $12.6 million attributable to the Corporation's equity in earnings of Midland Walwyn Inc, as compared to $9.7m of which $0.9m pertained to the equity in earnings of Midland Walwyn Inc. for the 2nd quarter last year. Earnings per share were $0.21 as compared to $0.16 for the same period last year.<BR><BR><DD>Net sales of Canadian managed mutual funds were $407 million for the 3 month period ended Sept 30, 96 as compared to $373m for the same period last year. Net sales of US-managed mutual funds were $228m (Cdn) as compared to $85 for the same period last year.<BR><BR><DD>Mutual fund assets under administration in Canada increased 32% tp $14.3 billion as of Sept 30, 96 from $10.8 billion as of Sept 30, 95. Mutual fund assets under administration in the United States increased by 5% to $2.6 billion (Cdn) from $1.8 billion (Cdn) as of Sept 30, 95.<BR><BR><DD>For additional information contact (416) 922-5322:
James L Hunter, Executive Vice President and COO;
James T Dryburgh, Senior Vice President and CFO
 
		 
		</TD>
		


		</TR>

			<TR>
		
		<TD COLSPAN = 2 ALIGN = "LEFT">
	 
	 	<IMG SRC = "../images/Divider.gif">

