<A HREF="../Search/index.html"><IMG SRC="../images/NoSlide.gif" WIDTH=90 HEIGHT=23 BORDER=0></A><BR>
<A HREF="../Search/index.html"><IMG SRC="../images/Search.gif" WIDTH=90 HEIGHT=13 BORDER=0 ALT="Search"></A><BR>

</TD>


 
<TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN = "RIGHT" WIDTH=100%>
<A HREF = "index.html"><IMG SRC="images/Community.gif" BORDER = 0 ALIGN=RIGHT></A>
<BR CLEAR=ALL>
<P>	
<BR>		 

		<TABLE WIDTH = 90% CELLSPACING = 10 BORDER =0>
			
		 
		<TR>

	
			

		<TD COLSPAN =1 ALIGN = "LEFT" VALIGN = "TOP" WIDTH = 75%>
	 
		<FONT SIZE = 3  >
		<NOBR><A HREF = "">Charitable Donations Program</A></NOBR>
		</FONT>
			 
		<FONT SIZE =2>
	 	<BR>
		<BR>
		<CITE>	
		<A HREF = ""></A>
		</CITE> 
		</FONT>
		</TD>
			
		<TD ROWSPAN = 2 ALIGN = "RIGHT" VALIGN = "TOP">
			
		<NOBR>
		
		<CODE>
		<FONT SIZE = 4>
		<A HREF = "/cgi-bin/MKNet/Who/Commune/Outside/viewArticle.cgi?846514586"><IMG SRC = "../images/Left.gif" BORDER = 0></A>  
		<A HREF = "/cgi-bin/MKNet/Who/Commune/Outside/displayArticles.cgi"><IMG SRC = "../images/Home.gif" BORDER = 0></A> 
		<A HREF = "/cgi-bin/MKNet/Who/Commune/Outside/viewArticle.cgi?846514157"><IMG SRC = "../images/Right.gif" BORDER = 0></A>
		</FONT>
		</CODE>

		</CODE>

		</NOBR>

		</TD>
 
		</TR>
	
		 
		<TR>
		
		<TD COLSPAN = 2 ALIGN = "LEFT">
	 
	 	<IMG SRC = "../images/Divider.gif">

		</TD>


		</TR>

			<TR>

	 	

		<TD COLSPAN =2 ALIGN = "LEFT" VALIGN = "TOP" WIDTH = 80%>

		<FONT SIZE = 2>
	  
	 	
		<DD><DD>A good measure of a company's financial and social integrity is the way it supports the communities in which it does business. As Mackenzie has grown, so has its commitment to helping those in need. Our Charitable Donations Committee sets objectives for our donations program and reviews applications for assistance.  In addition, Mackenzie has embraced three worthy cause in particular, Canadian Special Olympics, Blind and Disabled Ski Program and the Mackenzie Challenge. <BR><BR><DD>Through the charitable donations program, Mackenzie shares its financial success in a lasting and meaningful way with communities across the country. In 1995 alone, the Company gave more than $350,000 in direct cash donations to 93 different Canadian charities, as well as providing sponsorship through special marketing programs for three major charitable events.<BR><BR><DD>Mackenzie's Charitable Donations Committee is made up of staff throughout the organization, setting guidelines for eligibility to receive funds and reviewing the may request for assistance that the company receives during the year. One per cent of Mackenzie's annual pre-tax profits has been allocated to the Committee for distribution. Donations of varying sizes have been made to a wide variety of causes with emphasis focussing on health and welfare, chirldren's causes and the environment.

 
		 
		</TD>
		


		</TR>

			<TR>
		
		<TD COLSPAN = 2 ALIGN = "LEFT">
	 
	 	<IMG SRC = "../images/Divider.gif">

		</TD>


		</TR>


		</TABLE>


		</CENTER>


 



</FONT>

</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>


</TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

