Department of Horticultural Science, University of Minnesota, St. Paul, MN 55108<P>
<H2>Mission</H2>
The primary mission of the department is to discover, interpret, and transfer new knowledge for the purpose of:  (a) improving the productivity, value, and utilization of horticultural crops; (b) contributing to a quality environment; (c) educating students. <P> 
</CENTER>

For more information write:<P>
<A HREF="gardner.htm">Gary Gardner</A>, Dept. Head, 305 Alderman Hall, Univ. of MN, St. Paul, MN 55108<P>
612-624-5300    612-624-4941 (fax)<P><P>


