<TITLE>Deb Brown</TITLE>
<body bgcolor = "#ffffff" >
<H1>Deborah L. Brown (Deb), Associate Professor and Extension
Educator</H1><P>

M.S., University of Minnesota, 1979.  <P>

University of Minnesota, Department of Horticultural Science, 158
Alderman Hall, 1970 Folwell Ave., St. Paul, MN  55108; Telephone: 
612-624-7491; E-Mail:  brown015@maroon.tc.umn.edu; Fax: 
612-624-4941.<P>

Ms. Brown supervises the horticultural component of the Dial U
Insect and Plant Information Clinic, a state-wide consumer
answering service.  She communicates horticultural information to
the general public primarily via work in newspapers, radio and
television, and works closely with county extension personnel and
Master Gardeners.<P>

She hosts (and co-produces with Dr. Mary Meyer) a half-hour
television program, Minnesota Gardening, that runs weekly on local
cable channels throughout the state.

Long a member of the Garden Writers' Association of America, Ms.
Brown chairs the local committee planning the organization's
national meetings which will be held in Minneapolis/St. Paul in
August of 1996.  If you're interested in "garden communications" or
the Twin Cities meetings, please contact Deb for more information.

<H2>Courses Taught</H2><P>
<A HREF="hort1023.htm">Hort 1023</A>: Indoor Plants and Landscapes
<P>

<H2>References</H2><P>

Brown, D.L. and A.M. Hanchek.  1995.  Minnesota Gardening 1996,
AG-MI-5741-S; 7th annual calendar produced jointly by Minnesota
Experiment Station and Extension Service.<P>



