<H1>John E. Erwin, Assistant Professor</H1> <P>

Ph.D., Michigan State University, 1989 <P>

University of Minnesota, Department of Horticultural Science, 460 Alderman Hall, 1970 Folwell Ave.; Telephone: 612-624-9703; E-Mail: erwin001@maroon.tc.umn.edu; Fax: 612-624-4941.  <P>

A Floriculture physiologist and extension specialist, Dr. Erwin is responsible for coordinating the commercial floriculture extension program.  His research interests emphasize environmental physiology of greenhouse crops.  Specifically, Dr. Erwin is researching how plant stem elongation and flower initiation are influenced by light quality and temperature.  His research is applied and basic in nature.  He is a member of the horticulture graduate faculty.<P>

<H2>Courses Taught</H2>
 
<A HREF="hort8064.htm">Hort 8064</A>.  Discussions in Floricultural Science. <P>

