<H1>Susan M. Galatowitsch, Assistant Professor</H1>
<IMG ALIGN=top SRC ="galatowi.gif"><P>

University of Minnesota, Department of Horticultural Science, 260 Alderman Hall, 19070 Folwell Ave.,St. Paul, MN  55108; Telephone:  612-624-3242; E-Mail: galat0001@maroon.tc.umn.edu.<P>

Ph.D.  Iowa State University, 1993<P>

Dr. Galatowitsch is a landscape ecologist with a focus on the revegetation of natural communities.  She currently is investigating problems of plant dispersal and establishment in restored wetlands and is working to develop sources of wetland plant materials.  Dr. Galatowitsch teaches graduate courses in restoration and reclamation ecology, sustainable horticulture, and landscape ecology.  She holds a joint appointment in the Department of Horticultural Science and the Department of Landscape Architecture.  She is also a member of the horticulture and landscape architecture graduate faculty.<P>

<H2>Classes taught</H2><P>

