<H1>Anne M. Hanchek, Assistant Professor</H1> <P>
<IMG ALIGN=top SRC ="hanchek.gif"><P>

University of Minnesota, Department of Horticultural Science, 362 Alderman Hall, 1970 Folwell Ave., St. Paul, MN  55108; Telephone:  612-624-1706; E-Mail: hanch001@maroon.tc.umn.edu; Fax:  612-624-4941.<P>

Ph.D., Michigan State University, 1989. <P>

Dr. Hanchek is responsible for developing and coordinating statewide multi-media educational programs for professionals and amateurs in environmental horticulture.  Her research interests include production, growth, and development of herbaceous
flowering plants, especially native grasses and wildflowers.<P>

Dr. Hanchek has an office both on the St. Paul Campus and at the Minnesota Landscape Arboretum, where she maintains the State Master Gardener Office and participates in educational programming. She is a member of the horticulture graduate faculty. <P>
