<H1>Florian I. Lauer, Professor</H1><P>

<IMG ALIGN=top SRC ="lauer.gif"><P>

Address:  University of Minnesota, Department of Horticultural Science, 338 Alderman Hall, 1970 Folwell Ave., St. Paul, MN  55108; Telephone: 612-624-3612; E-Mail
lauer002@maroon.tc.umn.edu; Fax: 612-624-4941.<P>

Ph.D.  University of Minnesota, 1957.  <P>

Dr. Lauer teaches graduate courses in breeding of horticultural crops.  His research specialties include breeding, genetics, propagation systems, and field physiology of the potato, as well as disseminating this information to industry.  He has published extensively on these subjects.  Dr. Lauer is a member of the Inter-Regional Technical Committee, which is concerned with the introduction, preservation, classification, distribution, and evaluation of Solanum species, and the crop advisory committee for potatoes . He is past President of the Potato Association of America. Dr. Lauer is also a member of the gradate faculty in plant breeding.<P>
<P>

