<H1>James J. Luby,  Professor</H1><P>

Address:  University of Minnesota, Department of Horticultural Science, 254 Alderman Hall, 1970 Folwell Ave., St. Paul, MN  55108; Telephone 612-624-3453; E-Mail:  lubyx001@maroon.tc.umn.edu<P>

Ph.D., University of Minnesota, 1982.<P>

Dr. Luby teaches plant genetics. His research interests include utilization of wild germplasm in fruit crop improvement, development of efficient techniques to screen breeding material for resistance to cold temperature injury, and the relationship of plant growth and development to avoidance of winter injury.  Active breeding programs are conducted in blueberries, strawberries, grapes, brambles, and apples.  Dr. Luby is a member of the horticulture and plant breeding graduate faculty.<P>
<P>

<H2>Courses Taught</H2><P>

<A HREF="hort8063.htm">Hort 8063</A>.  Seminar:  Discussion in Horticultural Plant Breeding.<P>
<A HREF="hort3003.htm">Hort 3003</A>. Plant Genetics and Improvement<P>

