<CENTER>
<H1>Albert H. Markhart, III</H1><P>
<H2>Professor</H2><P>
<IMG SRC ="bud3.gif">  <P>
<IMG ALIGN=top SRC ="xmass96s.jpg">
 <A HREF="budmsg1.aif">Click here hear greeting.</A><P>
258 Alderman Hall, University of Minnesota, St. Paul, MN 55108 <P>
612-624-7705 (office) <P>
612-624-4941 (fax) <P>
<A HREF ="mailto: amarkhar@maroon.tc.umn.edu">amarkhar@maroon.tc.umn.edu </a> <P>
</CENTER>
Ph.D. Duke University, 1978; Alexander Von Humboldt Fellow, Hannover, West Germany, 1979.  Dr. Markhart teaches undergraduate and graduate courses in environmental physiology and plant water relations, and directs the department computer lab.  His research focuses on the acclimation and adaptation of plants to hostile fluctuating environments, with emphasis on the role of the root system in plant adjustment to water and temperature stresses.  
 <P>
In addition to a number of publications on water and temperature relations in plants, Dr. Markhart has written several computer programs for teaching water relations.  He holds one patent for a novel tissue extraction press.  Dr. Markhart is also a member of the Plant Biological Sciences graduate faculty.
 <P>
<H2>Courses Taught:</H2>
<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="hort3001.htm">Horticulture 3001</A>:  Growth Regulation of Horticultural Plants
<LI> <A HREF="pb5183.htm">Plant Biological Sciences 5183</A>:  Water, Minerals and Translocation
<LI> <A HREF="bio1203.htm">Biology 1203</A>:  Organismal Adaptation and Diversity
<LI> <A HREF="hort3010.htm">Horticuture 3010</A>:  Growing Plants Organically;  What It Means To Be "Green"

</UL>
<H2>Selected Publications:</H2>
Markhart, III A.H. 1984.  Amelioration of chilling-induced water stress by abscisic acid-induced changes in root hydraulic conductance.  Plant Physiol. 74:81-83
 <P>
Lin, T.Y. and A. H. Markhart, III. 1990.  Temperature effects on mitochondrial respiration in <I>Phaseolus acutifolius</I> and <I>P. vulgaris</I> L. Plant Physiol. 94:54-58
 <P>
Castonguay, Y. and A. H. Markhart, III. 1991.  Saturated rates of photosynthesis in water-stressed leaves of common bean and tepary bean.  Crop Sci. 31:1605-1611
 <P>
Castonguay, Y. and A. H. Markhart, III. 1992. Leaf gas exchange in water-stressed common bean and tepary bean.  Crop Sci. 32:980-986.
 <P>
Sanders, P.L. and A. H. Markhart, III. 1992. Interspecific grafts demonstrated root system control of leaf water status in water- stressed Phaseolus. J. Exp. Bot. 43:1563-1567.
 <P>
Udomprasert, N, PL Li, DW Davis, AH Markhart, III 1995. Effect of root temperatures on leaf gas exchange and growth at high air temperatures in <I>Phaseolus acutifolius</I> and <I>Phaseolus vulgaris</I>. Crop Sci. 35:486-489
<P>

Markhart III, AH and M Harper. 1995. Deleterious effects of sucrose in preservative solutions on leaves of cut roses.  Hort Sci 30:1429-1432.
<P>

