<H1>Mary Hockenberry-Meyer, Assistant Professor</H1><P>

<IMG ALIGN=top SRC ="meyer.gif"><P>

University of Minnesota, Department of Horticultural Science,  354 Alderman Hall, 1970 Folwell Ave., St. Paul, MN  55108; Telephone: 612-624-3665; E-Mail:  meyer023@maroon.tc.umn.edu; Fax: 612-624-4941<P>

Ph.D., University of Minnesota.  1993.  <P>

Dr. Meyer is responsible for developing and coordinating statewide multi-media educational programs for professionals and amateurs in environmental horticulture.  Her research interests include native and exotic ornamental grasses, especially
Miscanthus and Pennisetum.  She is interested in cold hardiness, isozyme and analysis and plant breeding research with ornamental and native grasses, as well as low maintenance alternative lawn grasses.  Dr. Meyer has an office both on the St. Paul Campus and at the Minnesota Landscape Arboretum, where she maintains the State Master Gardener Office and participates in educational programming. <P>

