<H1>Bert T. Swanson, II, Professor</H1> <P><P>

<IMG ALIGN=top SRC ="swanson.gif"><P>

University of Minnesota, Department of Horticultural Science,    Alderman Hall, 1970 Folwell Ave., St. Paul, MN  55108; Telephone: 612-624-7432;  Fax:  612-624-4941.<P>

Ph.D., University of Minnesota, 1972<P>

Dr. Swanson teaches undergraduate and graduate courses in nursery management and production and advises students in the area of nursery and landscape
management.  He conducts research relative to the nursery and landscape industries and has an extension appointment working with the nursery and landscape industry in Minnesota and the north central U.S.  Dr. Swanson's research focuses on the use of herbicides in nursery crops, winter injury on conifers, container media and fertility, and physiological aspects of production and harvesting of nursery crops.  He directs the 10-acre Teaching, Research, and Extension (TRE) Nursery on the St. Paul campus and publishes monthly in the North Central Nurseryman and Extend.<P>

Dr. Swanson has received the American Association of Nurseryman Education Award, the College of Agriculture Distinguished Teaching Award, and the University of Minnesota Horace T. Morse Award for excellence in undergraduate education.  He is a member of the horticulture graduate faculty.<P>
<P>

<H2>Courses Taught </H2><P>

<A HREF="hort5046.htm">Hort 5046</A>.  Nursery Management I.  <P>
<A HREF="hort5047.htm">Hort 5047</A>.  Nursery Scheduling and Enterprise Development.<P>
 
<A HREF="hort5048.htm">Hort 5048</A>.  Nursery Management and Production II.  <P>


