<H1>Cindy Tong, Assistant Professor</H1><P>

<IMG ALIGN=top SRC ="tong.gif"><P>

University of Minnesota, Department of Horticultural Science, 434 Alderman Hall, 1970 Folwell Ave., St. Paul, MN  55108; Telephone: 612-624-3419; E-Mail:  ctong@maroon.tc.umn.edu; Fax:  612-624-4941.<P>

Ph.D., University of California, Davis, 1986<P>

In cooperation with other extension personnel, Dr. Tong develops and conducts educational programs for Minnesota growers on postharvest handling of vegetable crops.  Her research currently focuses on solving practical postharvest problems in potatoes and understanding the basic biochemical mechanisms involved in fruit ripening.  Specifically, she is studying the biochemical structure and mechanism of action of an endogenous trigger of ripening-related ethylene production in
tomato fruit.  She also co-teaches an introductory postharvest physiology class and is a member of the horticulture and plant biological sciences graduate faculty.<P>

<H2>Classes Taught</H2> <P>

<A HREF="hort5001.htm">Hort 5001</A>.  Harvest to Market of Horticultural Crops.<P>

<A HREF="hort8065.htm">Hort 8065</A>.  Seminar:  Discussions in Postharvest Physiology. <P>

