<H1>Donald B. White, Professor, Ph.D.</H1><P>

<IMG ALIGN=top SRC ="white.gif"><P>

University of Minnesota, Department of Horticultural Science, 456 Alderman Hall, 1970 Folwell Ave., St. Paul, MN  55108; Telephone: 612-624-9206; E-Mail:  007@maroon.tc.umn.edu;  Fax:  612-624-4941.<P>

Iowa State University, 1961.  <P>

Dr. White teaches graduate and undergraduate courses in turf grass science.  His research currently focuses on cold acclimation and deacclimation of turf grass with
emphasis on the role nutrition plays in the process.  Research also includes postharvest heating of sod; chemical regulation of growth; breeding and genetics in ornamental and turfgrasses; cultural systems in turf grass management;
flowering in Poa annua; the physiology of germination; ecology of turf grass communities; and the breeding and genetics of Poa annua for golf turf.  Graduate students are currently associated with research in: inheritance of
flowering in Poa annua; physiology of seed germination; breeding and genetics of Pennisetum allopecuroides; cold tolerance in grasses; the population dynamics of Poa annua/bentgrass competition under golf green management; and breeding and genetics of Poa annua improvement.  He is a member of the horticulture graduate faculty.<P>
<P>

<H2>Courses Taught</H2><P>

<A HREF="hort5042.htm">Hort 5042</A>.  Turf Grass Science.<P>
<A HREF="hort3072.htm">Hort 3072</A>.  Turf Management.<P>

<H2>Selected References</H2><P>

Allen, P.S. and D.B. White.  Patent 1990 (pending) No. 07/813,350, A Method for Accelerating and Synchronizing Seed Germination.<P>

Ruemmele, B.A., P.D. Ascher and D.B. White. 1991.  Some observations on the reproductive biology of Poa  annua L. Commemorative Volume Prof. Verma, Book Chapter.<P>

Cline, V.W., D.B. White and H. Kaewer. 1993.  Observations of population dynamics of selected annual bluegrass  creeping bentgrass golf greens in Minnesota. Proc. International Turfgrass Research Society.<P>

