TITLE>OPEN RA</TITLE><P>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFE8">
<H3>Open Research Assistantship (Open RA) Program
</H3><P>

The University of Minnesota Department of Horticultural Science
offers one to three assistantships annually for highly qualified
students who intend to pursue a Ph.D. or M.S. (with thesis). 
Stipends are approximately $12,218 plus a health plan and waiver of
tuition.  Three years of support are provided for the M.S. and four
years are provided for the Ph.D.  Up to one year of option
exploration is available with no project-related responsibilities. 
During this time the student is required to complete three
rotations with different faculty members and becomes familiar with
their research programs and interests.  During, or shortly after,
the rotations the student selects a thesis advisor with the mutual
agreement of the advisor.  
 
     Open RAs are awarded competitively each January for the
following September.  An applicant should have all graduate program
application materials submitted by December 15 to be considered. <P>

</DOC>
