<H2>Hort 3010.  Growing Plants Organically:  What It Means To Be "Green"</H2><P>

Instructor:<P>

<A HREF="markhart.htm">Dr. Albert H. Markhart, III</A><P>

This couse focuses on the science and ethics of organic cultivation. Students learn what is meant by "green" from a legal, scientific, and ethical perspective.  Students explore original literature on an organic practice, prepare a written report, and lead a class discussion.  (Prerequisite:  Hort 1036 or Biol 1103 or Bio 3012 or equivl.  Advanced standing: junior or senior status is required or permission of instructor.)
<P>


