<H2>Hort 5031  Temperate Fruit Production</H2>

Instructor

<A HREF="hoover.htm">Dr. Emily Hoover</A>

Principles of fruit production, emphasizing temperate fruit crops.  Integrated management of fruit cropping systems, including site selection, cultural and management practices, taxonomic classification, physiological and environmental control of plant development.  Intensive use of writing. (4 credits; prereq 3001; PBio 3131 recommended; offered odd yrs.). 

