<H2>Hort 5034.  Commercial Vegetable Agriculture</H2> 
  
Instructor<P>

<A HREF="davis.htm">Dr. Dave Davis</A><P>

Crop cultural and product handling and use systems in various world regions.  History and evolution of species and product development.  Seed and stand establishment; propagation; pest management.  Applied physiology and genetics of fruit, bulb, tuber initiation; sink development, maturation, and quality.  Lectures, labs, and field trips. (5 credits; prereq 3002 or Agro 1010, Soil 3125)<P>

