<HTML>
<HEAD><TITLE>Arboretum Events & Classes</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFE8"><P>

<center><H2>Minnesota Landscape Arboretum<BR>
University of Minnesota<BR>
Schedule of Events & Classes<P>

December 1996 - February 1997
</H2>
</center><P>

<I><CENTER>PLEASE NOTE:  EVENTS & CLASSES ARE SUBJECT TO CHANGE OR CANCELLATION.  CALL AHEAD FOR  AN UPDATE IF IT IS IMPORTANT TO YOUR PLANS!<BR>
<STRONG>Telephone: (612) 443-2460, ext. 0</STRONG></CENTER>
</I><P>

<CENTER>Got a gardening question?  </CENTER><BR>
Call it in to the <EM>Northern Lights Gardening</EM> radio show and speak to the experts.  Ralph Bashioum and Jody Fetzer from the Arboretum will help you understand it all "from the simple to the scientific."  You'll find them every Saturday at 8:00-9:00 am on KLBB; 1400 am in the metro, or 1470 am north of metro.<P>

<CENTER><EM>Teatime at the Garden</EM></CENTER><BR>
Enjoy a traditional English Tea this winter in the warm, comfortable surroundings of the Arboretum.  Teas include scones and Devonshire cream, Maids of Honour, tea sandwiches and breads, Palmiers, tarts and English trifle.  Wednesdays from 3:00 to 4:30 pm at the Arboretum.  Cost is $10 per person.  Call reservations/information at (612) 443-2460, ext. 772.<P>

<H2><CENTER>DECEMBER (Closed Christmas Day)</CENTER></H2><P>

<STRONG>AUXILIARY HOLIDAY SALE</STRONG><BR>
<STRONG>Saturday, December 7;  9:00 am to 4:30 pm</STRONG><BR>
Choose from a great selection of wreaths in many sizes, centerpieces, candles, ornaments, bookmarks, pressed-flower cards, door swags and fresh greens.  All items have been hand-crafted by Arboretum Auxiliary members.  (Credit cards are not accepted--cash, check or Auxiliary gift certificates only.)<P>

<STRONG>HOLIDAY OPEN HOUSE</STRONG><BR>
<STRONG>Saturday & Sunday, December 7 & 8;  11:00 am to 3:00 pm</STRONG><BR>
Before plunging into the busiest part of the holiday season, take time to have some fun.  Share a holiday song with family or friends as you take a ride around the Arboretum in an old-fashioned horse-drawn wagon.  Rides are an additional cost per person; 11:00 am to 3:00 pm on Saturday and Sunday.  From 12 Noon to 3:00 pm each day, families can participate in hands-on activities making natural crafts to take home, sponsored by the Arboretum's Learning Center.  Holiday musical groups will entertain you; the fresh air on a walk or cross country skiing on trails will revitalize you; a good book in the library will relax you; and a bowl of hot, homemade soup in the Tearoom as you view the winter afternoon setting and the constant, lively activity at the bird feeders will delight you.  Discover the spirit of the holiday and winter season at the Arboretum.<P>

<STRONG>FESTIVAL OF TREES<BR>
Wednesday, December 11 - Tuesday, December 31</STRONG><BR>
<STRONG>During regular Snyder building hours<BR>
Closed Christmas Day</STRONG><BR>
The Snyder building auditorium will be transformed into a wonderful holiday display of fresh evergreen trees.  Each tree will be decorated with handmade and natural materials (no lights) by various garden clubs, herb societies and other non-profit groups in celebration of the holiday spirit.  Take a self-guided tour, or volunteer-guided tours are available by advance registration at no additional tour charge.  Display is free with regular paid Arboretum gate admission.<P>

<H2><CENTER>JANUARY</CENTER></H2><P>

<STRONG>FAMILY FUN: Track Detectives, Bog Area<BR>
Sunday, January 5;  1:00 - 3:00 pm</STRONG><BR>
Meet in Snyder Building Lobby<BR>
Informal activity, fun for the whole family.  Dress for the outdoors to identify various animal tracks in a selected part of the Arboretum.  Activity free with regular paid gate admission.<P>

<STRONG>TRAVELOGUE Slide Lecture:  Garden Tour Preview<BR>
Sunday, January 12;  1:30 - 3:00 pm         Auditorium</STRONG><BR>
This is a preview of four 1997 Arboretum-sponsored tours to Charleston & Savannah, England & Scottland, Pacific Northwest and Vancouver, and San Francisco and the Bay area.  Free with regular paid gate admission.<P>

<STRONG>FAMILY FUN:  Dried Plant Weavings<BR>
Sunday, January 19;  1:00 - 3:00 pm</STRONG><BR>
Meet in Snyder Building Lobby<BR>
Informal activity, fun for the whole family.  Dress for a visit to the outdoors to collect materials to weave on a natural loom.  Activity free with regular paid gate admission.<P>

<STRONG>JAPANESE GARDEN SERENITY TOUR<BR>
Monday, January 20</STRONG><BR>
A Japanese garden is meant to be viewed during all the seasons, and takes on special qualities during the winter.  Experience the serenity of the garden as Japanese Garden volunteers take you on a guided tour walk through the Arboretum's own Japanese Garden to view the garden in its winter splendor and discover some unique features of the garden.  Dress for the weather, and join one of the tours at 1<STRONG>0:30, 11:00 or 11:30 am.</STRONG>  Tours are free with regular paid gate admission.  Visitors will also be able to view an hour-long video on the Japanese culture.<P>

<STRONG>HOLIDAY PROGRAM: Family "Green-Up" Day   <BR>   
Monday, January 20;  9:00 am to 12 Noon         Auditorium</STRONG><BR>
<EM>For kids and their familes, sponsored by the Arboretum's Learning Center--free with paid gate admission.</EM><BR>
Does your home look a little bare with winter settled in and all your holiday trappings put away?  You can remedy that at the Arboretum's Family "Green-Up" Day.  Visit activity stations to start your own plants from cuttings and plant-able groceries, search for fragrant orchids and other tropical wonders in the Conservatory, zoom in on the magical world inside plants through Dr. Dissecto's microscopes, and stop by the Storytime Corner with tales of garden adventures.<P>

<STRONG>TRAVELOGUE Slide Lecture:  Charleston & Savannah<BR>
Sunday, January 26;  1:30 - 3:00 pm            Auditorium</STRONG><BR>
Free with regular paid gate admission.<P>

<H2><CENTER>FEBRUARY</CENTER></H2><P>

<STRONG>FAMILY FUN:  Track Detectives, Main Gardens<BR>
Sunday, February 2;  1:00 - 3:00 pm</STRONG><BR>
Meet in Snyder Building Lobby<P>

<STRONG>SPECIALTY GARDENS LECTURE SERIES: Choices for Gardens<BR>             
Hennepin Technical College, Brooklyn Park<BR>        
Saturday, February 8;  8:30 am to 2:15 pm</STRONG><BR>
Call 643-3601 for more information and a brochure.<P>

<STRONG>TRAVELOGUE Slide Lecture:  England & Scotland<BR>
Sunday, February 9;  1:30 - 3:00 pm           Auditorium</STRONG><BR>
Free with regular paid gate admission.<P>

<STRONG>MINNEAPOLIS HOME & GARDEN SHOW<BR>
Wednesday - Sunday, February 12 - 16    Mpls Convention Ctr</STRONG><P>

<STRONG>FAMILY FUN:  DRIED PLANT WEAVINGS<BR>
Sunday, February 16;  1:00 - 3:00 pm</STRONG><BR>
Meet in Snyder Building Lobby<P>

<STRONG>HOLIDAY PROGRAM:  To be Determined<BR>
Monday, February 17; time to be determined</STRONG><P>

<STRONG>1997 GREENING CONFERENCE:  Plants for Change<BR>
Saturday, February 22;  8:30 am to 5:00 pm</STRONG><BR>
Held at the Hennepin Technical Center, Brooklyn Park<BR>
Collaboration with DNR, DOT, Minnesota State Horticultural Society, Minnesota Recreation and Parks Association and the Minnesota Landscape Arboretum.  Call (612) 643-3601 or 1-800-676-6747 outstate for more information.<P>

<STRONG>TRAVELOGUE Slide Lecture:  To Be Determined<BR>
Sunday, February 23;  1:30 - 3:00 pm            Auditorium</STRONG><BR>
Free with regular paid gate admission. <P>

