<H1>Plant Bioloical Sciences 5183  (PBio 5183)  Water Minerals and Translocation</H1><P>

<H2>Instructors:</H2><P>

<UL>
<LI> <A HREF="markahrt.htm">Dr. Albert H. Markhart, III</A>
<LI> <A HREF="dallan.htm">Dr. Debra Allan</A><P>

</UL><P>

<H2>Course Description:</H2>
(4 credits,  Prereq. 5131 or equiv.)  Membrane phenomena and osmotic properties of cells.  Uptake, movement and loss of water in plants, including the effects of external factors.  Translocation of organic substances. Absorption, distribution, and function of inorganic elements.<P>

<I>Return to <A HREF="crslist.htm">Course</A> list</I>
Currently meets:<P>

MWF 1:55-2:50
Th 1:15-2:30
</DOC>
