<H1>Vincent Fritz, Associate Professor</H1>
<IMG ALIGN=top SRC ="fritz.gif"><P>

Ph.D., Michigan State University, 1985<P>

University of Minnesota, Department of Horticulture, Southern Experiment Station, Waseca, MN 56093 Telephone: 507-835-3620; Fax: 507-835-3622.<P>

Dr. Fritz is located at the Southern Experiment Station in Waseca, which is 75 miles south of St. Paul.  Working in a field-oriented research program, he investigates the physiological effects of sweet corn, peas, potatoes, and other vegetable crop production systems on both mineral and organic soils.  He is a member of the horticulture graduate faculty.<P>

<H2>Selected References</H2><P>

Fritz, Vincent A., Harold A. Cloud, Robert F. Deef and Alicia M. Borowski. 1990. A versatile heat pump seed dryer. HortScience 25:977-978.<P>

Borowski, A.M., V.A. Fritz and L. Waters, Jr. 1991.  Seed maturity influences germination and vigor of two shrunken-2 sweet corn hybrids. J. Amer. Soc. Hort. Sci. 116:401-404.<P>

Fritz, V.A. and C.J. Rosen. 1991.  Productivity of processing peas as influenced by nitrogen fertilization,  Rhizobium inoculation, and fungicide seed treatment. Can. J. Plant Sci. 71:1271-1274.<P>

