<head><title>
RESTORATION AND RECLAMATION ECOLOGY - READING LIST</title>
</head>
<body>
<h3 align="center">HORTICULTURE 5015</h3> 
<h2 align="center">RESTORATION AND RECLAMATION ECOLOGY</h2>
<h3 align="center">READING LIST</h3><hr size=10 noshade>

<h2>INTRODUCTION</h2>

<h3>REQUIRED READING</h3>
Holloway, M.  1994.  Nurturing Nature.  Scientific American (April).  98-108.
<p>
<h3>OTHER REFERENCES</h3>
Jordan, W., M. Gilpin, and J. Abers. 1987.  Restoration Ecology:  a synthetic approach to 
ecological research.  Cambridge University Press, New York.<p>
Bradshaw, A.D.  1983.  The reconstruction of ecosystems.  Journal of Applied Ecology 20:  1-17.<p>
Bradshaw, A.D.  1984.  Ecological principles and land reclamation practices.  Landscape Planning  11:  35-48.<p>
Buckley, G.P.  1989.  Biological Habitat Reconstruction.  Belhaven Press, London.<p>
Cooke, G.D., E.B. Welch, S.A. Peterson, and P.R. Newroth.  1986.  Lake and Reservoir 
Restoration.  Butterworth, Stoneham, Mass.<p>
Diamond, J.  1985.  How and why eroded ecosystems should be restored.  Nature 313:  629-630.<p>
Howell, E.A.  Woodland restoration:  an overview.  Restoration and management Notes 4(1):  13-17.<p>
Howell, E.A.  1988.  The role of restoration in conservation biology.  Endangered Species Update 5:  1-4.<p>
Johnson, M.S. and A.D. Bradshaw.  1979.  Ecological principles for the restoration of disturbed 
and degraded lands.  Applied Biology 4:  141.<p>
Munshower, F.F.  1994.  Practical handbook of disturbed land revegetation.  Lewis Publishers. <p> 
National Research Council.  1992.  Restoration of Aquatic Ecosytems.  National Academy Press, 
Washington, D.C.<p>
Perry, D.A., M.P. Amaranthus, J.G. Borchers, S.L. Borchers, and R.E. Brainerd.  1989.  <p>
Bootstrapping in ecosystems.  BioScience  39:  23-237.<p>
Schaller, F.W.  and P. Sutton.  1978.   Reclamation of drastically disturbed lands.  American 
Society for Agronomy.  Madison, Wisconsin.<p>
Thompson, J.  1992.  Prairies, Forests, and Wetlands:  the Restoraiton of Natural Landscape 
Communities in Iowa.  University of Iowa Press, Iowa City.<p><hr>


<h2>RESTORATION PLANNING</h2>

<h3>REQUIRED READING</h3>
Bedford, B.L.  1996.  The need to define hydrologic equivalence at the landscape scepe for 
freshwater wetland mitigation.  Ecological Applications 6:  57-68.<p>

Galatowitsch, S.M. 1990. Using the original land survey notes to reconstruct presettlement 
landscapes in the American west.  Great Basin Naturalist 50(2): 181-191.<p>

