<HTML>
<HEAD>
<title>DIS History</title>
<meta name="Author" content="Matt Martelli">
<meta name="Project" content="home">
<meta name="Server" content="Internet">
<meta name="Date" content="8-30-96">
<link rel="previous" href="overview.htm">
</HEAD>
<BODY background="/images/texture.gif">

<center><H3>DEFENSE INVESTIGATIVE SERVICE</H3>
<H3>History</H3></center>
<hr>
<br>
<UL>
<P>The Department of Defense (DoD) recognized that having each military
service conduct its own background investigation during the processing
of a clearance request was extremely inefficient. In 1972 the DoD formed
the Defense Investigative Service (DIS) to conduct these investigations.
DIS also was charged with conducting national agency checks (NACs) on individuals.
NACs are conducted either as part of a clearance request or as the basis
to make a suitability decision for positions such as child care workers
or janitorial service workers that do not need a full background investigation.

<P>In 1980 DIS assumed the responsibility for contractor support of the
clearance process. The Defense Industrial Security Clearance Office (DISCO)
in Columbus, OH became part of DIS, as well as the Industrial Security
Program, which covers contractors and their facilities. Through the Industrial
Security Program, DIS helps contractors manage and protect classified data
while working on DoD contracts.
</UL>
<br>
<hr>
<p><a href="overview.htm"><img src="/images/back.gif" alt="back arrow" align=bottom border=0 width=40 height=40></a> Go back to the Dis Overview page</p>
<hr>
<address>Author: Matt Martelli<br>
Revised: 30 August 1996 </address>
</BODY>
</HTML>
</DOC>
