<html>

<head>
<title>DIS Officers Page</title>
<meta name="Author" content="Matt Martelli">
<meta name="Project" content="home">
<meta name="Server" content="Internet">
<meta name="Date" content="9-12-96">
<link rel="previous" href="overview.htm">
<link rel="next" href="mmunson.htm">
<link rel="next" href="sschanze.htm">
</head>

<body background="/images/texture.gif">
<center><H3>DEFENSE INVESTIGATIVE SERVICE</H3>
<H3>Officers</H3></center>
<hr>
<br>
<ul>
<p>The Defense Investigative Service is lead by the <b>Director</b>,
<a href="/people/mmunson.htm">Margaret Munson</a>.  The director's
office provides executive direction and control of all DIS 
programs and resources under the operational control of the Assistant
Secretary of Defense for Command, Control, Communications and Intelligence. 
DIS is responsible for execution of two principle programs:
<p><ul>
<li><b>Personnel Security Investigations</b>:  DIS has Special Agents located throughout
the U.S. (and Puerto Rico) in over 85 locations who are authorized to conduct
personnel security investigations to determine security clearance eligibility
of U.S. Military personnel, DoD civilian employees and defense contractors.
<p>
<li><b>Industrial Security Program</b>:  DIS administration of the National Industrial
Security Program provides assurance to all elements of the Department of Defense and
other federal departments and agencies, that their contractors and suppliers performing
on classified contracts have systems and procedures in place to effectively safeguard 
classified information.
</ul>
<p>The <b>Principle Deputy Director</b> of the Defense Investigative Service is
<a href="/people/sschanze.htm">Steve Schanzer</a>.  <i>There is
no releaseable information on the Principle Deputy Director's office
at this time.</i>
<br>
<p><a href="overview.htm"><img src="/images/back.gif" align=bottom border=0 width=40 height=40></a> Go back to the DIS Overview page.
<hr>
<address>Author: Matt Martelli<br>
Revised: 12 September 1996 </address>
</body>

