<TITLE>National Industrial Security Board</TITLE>
<meta name="Author" content="Ron Tuskan">
<meta name="Project" content="NISB">
<meta name="Server" content="Internet">
<meta name="Date" content="1-2-97">
</HEAD>

<BODY BACKGROUND="/images/texture.gif">
<a HREF="/index.htm" target="_top" onMouseOver="window.status='Back to the DIS home page'; return true"><IMG SRC="/images/back.gif" ALIGN="right" BORDER=0></A>
<p>
<center><H1>National Industrial Security System</H1> </center>
<p>
<HR>
<A HREF="tecwarn.htm"><h2>Security Warning</h2></A> Per the US Government a
security banner must be accompanied with every Government Network.  Read the security banner before continuing.
<HR>
The Defense Investigative Service has set up an electronic bulletin board to provide timely distribution of information relating to the
National Industrial Security Program.
<P>
The bulletin board has the current <A HREF="nispom/manual.htm">NISPOM (National Industrial
Security Operating Manual)</A> changes, interpretations, meetings, announcements, computer security information and a
place for you to post your questions and concerns.
<P>
The board is available to the entire industrial security community and other DoD components.  All you need is a computer and a modem to gain
access to the latest industrial security information.

<H3>NISB's Resources:</H3> 
<UL>
The NISB bulletin board system contains a wealth of information.  Some of the bulletin boards in the system contain up to date news.
<A HREF="bboards.htm">NISB bulletin boards</A> are open to all NISB users the day they sign up.
<br>
</ul>
<H3>Other Sources</H3>
<UL>
<li><a href="http://tecnet1.jcte.jcs.mil:8000">DoD-TECNET Home Page</a>
<li><a href="http://www.delfinsd.delfin.com/nsia">National Security Industrial Association</a>
<li><a href="http://www.assist.mil/ASSIST/">Assist</a>
</UL>
<hr>
If you have any questions or comments, please feel free to contact internet address: 
<A HREF="mailto:ispost@dislink.jcte.jcs.mil">
ispost@dislink.jcte.jcs.mil</A>  
<br><hr>
