</DOCHDR>
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//IETF//DTD HTML//EN">

<html>

<head>
<title>EPSQ DOWNLOAD PAGE</title>
<meta name="Author" content="William Howard">
<meta name="Project" content="EPSQ">
<meta name="Server" content="Internet">
<meta name="Date" content="7-25-96">
<link rel="previous" href="dissoft.htm">
<link rel="previous" href="epsqhome.htm">
</head>

<body background="/images/texture.gif" text="#000000" link="#0000EE" vlink="#551A8B" alink="#FF0000">

<h1 align=center>Download EPSQ</h1>
<hr>
<h3>This page is the page set up to allow you to download the latest version of EPSQ software, 
and the support documentation and files. </h3>
<hr>
<p><img src="/images/refer.gif" align=bottom width=54 height=54>
<p>If you have problems or questions concerning the EPSQ software, please call the DIS&#160;Customer Service Center at <strong>1-(800)&#160;542-0237</strong>.
<hr>
<h2>EPSQ 1.2 is divided into the following two editions:</h2>
<dl>
<dt><i>Subject Edition. (dated Feb 96)</i> 
<dd>The Subject edition of the EPSQ system is set up to allow the individual subject to enter all of the information that is required to request a security clearance. This information would normally appear on a Questionnaire for National Security Positions (Standard Form (SF) 86), Questionnaire for Public Trust Positions (SF 85P), or a Supplemental Questionnaire for Selected Positions (SF 85P-S). After the subject enters the information, they will be able to print, validate, and send the data to the Security Officer. 
<dt><i>Security Officer Edition. (dated Feb 96)</i> 
<dd>The Security Officer (SO) edition of the EPSQ system is set up to allow the Security Officer the ability to take the subject's data, and add the additional information that is required to request a security clearance. The SO can enter data for Request for Personnel Security Investigation (DD Form 1879), and the National Agency Check (NAC) administrative form. Also, the ability for completion of the Personnel Security Clearance Change Notification (DISCO Form 562) is included in this version of EPSQ. The Security Officer will be able to print, validate, certify, and send the data electronically to DIS for processing.
</dl>
<hr>
<h1><img src="/images/warning.gif" alt="warning" align=absbottom hspace=5 vspace=5 width=40 height=40>!! NOTICE !!</h1>
<p><font size=5><b>The SEC.EXE and SUB.EXE files are the complete versions of EPSQ 
1.2b.</b></font>
<p><font size=5><b>You must also download the EPSQ 1.2c Patch, which is necessary to 
implement the latest changes, as of March 14, 1996.</b></font>
<hr size=5 noshade>
<hr size=5 noshade>
<h2>Download EPSQ software or additional files:</h2>
<hr>
<h3 align=center>Test file:</h3>
<p><img src="/images/ball_blu.gif" alt="*" align=bottom width=14 height=14> <a href="ftp://www.dis.mil/pub/projects/epsq/testfile.zip">Test file</a> to check your being able to download from this page (1 K) 
<hr>
<h3 align=center>Complete list of files:</h3>
