<head>
<title>Marge Munson</title>
<meta name="Author" content="Matt Martelli">
<meta name="Project" content="home">
<meta name="Server" content="Internet">
<meta name="Date" content="8-30-96">
<link rel="previous" href="officers.htm">
</head>

<body background="/images/texture.gif">
<center><IMG SRC="/images/mmunson.jpg" ALT="[Picture]" BORDER=5>
<br>
<H2>                Margaret R. Munson</H2>
<H3>                	 Director<br>
		Defense Investigative Service</h3></center>

<p><dd>Margaret Munson became the Director of 
the Defense Investigative Service in March 1996. 
Her previous position was as the Director for 
Counterintelligence and Security Programs in 
the Office of the Assistant Secretary of Defense 
(Command, Control, Communications, and Intelligence).
<p><dd>From 1992-1994, Mrs. Munson was the Director 
for Planning and Administration of the Defense
Intelligence Agency.  Her responsibilities included
strategic planning; human resources, career development,
training and military reserve management; security and
counterintelligence; contracting and logistics services.

<p><dd>In 1991, she was selected by the Assistant
Secretary of Defense (Command, Control, Communications
and Intelligence) to organize and manage a special
Department of Defense office to assist the work of the 
Senate Select Committee on POW/MIA Affairs.  Her office
facilitated access by Senators and staff to Deparment
of Defense officials and documentation, and directed
review and declassification of records concerning
POW/MIAs.

<p><dd>From 1969-1991, she served in a variety of
intelligence positions with the Defense Intelligence Agency
to include Chief of Production Function Management Office
and Chief of the Data Base Management Division.  In
the latter capacity, she managed the JCS Distributed 
Production Program and the implementation of the Military 
Intelligence Integrated Data System (MIIDS)/Integrated 
Database (IDB) for use throughout DoD for Military planning 
and operations.

<p><dd>Mrs. Munson attended Creighton Univeristy in Omaha,
Nebraska and the University of Madrid in Spain, receiving a 
Bachelor of Arts Degree in Spanish in 1969.  She has a 
Masters of Science Degree in Administration (Information Systems
Technology) from George Washington University, Washington,DC,
and is a graduate of the National War College (Class of 1987).
She attended the Program for Senior Executives in National and
Industrial Security at the John F. Kennedy School of Government,
Harvard University in 1995.

<p><dd>Noteworthy awards which Mrs. Munson has received include
the DIA Director's Award for Exceptional Civilian Service in 1988,
Secretary of Defense Medal for Meritorious Civilian Service in 1992,
and the Department of Defense Distinguished Civilian Service award 
in 1995.
<br>
<br>
<hr>
