<body background="/images/texture.gif">
<h1><center>Deputy Director for Industrial Security</center></h1>
<h1><img src="/images/ggwash.gif" align=bottom width=100 height=123 border=5> Mr. Greg Gwash</h1>
<hr>
<h2>Biography</h2>
<p><p>Greg Gwash, a native of Minnesota, has a bachelor's degree
in Russian Area Studies, a master's degree in Far Eastern
History and a juris doctorate degree.  He is currently
responsible for the implementation of the Defense portion
of the National Industrial Security Program (NISP) delegated
to the Defense Investigative Service (DIS), as well as the
Key Asset Protection Program, the Arms, Ammunition and
Explosives Program, and the DIS Counterintelligence
Integration Program.

<p><a href="people/ggwash.htm">Complete biography</a>


<hr>
<h2>The Office of the Deputy Director for Industrial Security</h2>
<p>Responsible for all facets of the three DoD Industrial Security Programs assigned to DIS -- the National Industrial Security 
Program, the DoD Key Assets Protection Program, and the DoD Sensitive Conventional Arms, Ammunition, and Explosive 
Program. Also responsible for the DIS Counterintelligence Program. Acts as the senior operating official and principal staff 
advisor to the Director in the development and promulgation of major policy, plans, and programs. national and international 
in scope, relating to the administration of the three aforementioned DoD programs. In addition, supervises and directs the 
Defense Industrial Security Clearance Office and the Offices of Industrial Security International; provides program 
management supervision and overall guidance for all Industrial Security matters and personnel within DIS; and represents the 
Director in forums within and outside the government. 
<hr>
