<br>
<center><H2>                JAMES G. O'HERON</H2>
<H3>                     DEPUTY DIRECTOR OF DISCO<BR>
                       DEFENSE INVESTIGATIVE SERVICE</h3></center>

<p>	James F. OHeron is the Deputy Director of the
Defense Industrial Security Clearance Office (DISCO) in 
Columbus, Ohio.  He began his Federal Civil Service career 
as a adjudicator in the Adjudication Division of DISCO.  
He subsequently became DISCOs Privacy and Freedom of 
Information Coordinator, the functional analyst for DISCOs 
computer system, a senior adjudicator, a Branch Chief in 
the Adjudication Division, and the Assistant Chief of the 
personnel Clearance Division.   He left DISCO to become 
the Chief of Personnel Security Division III of the 
Defense Office of Hearings and Appeals,  Defense Legal 
Services Agency, and returned DISCO as the Chief of the 
Personnel Clearance Division.  He became the Deputy 
Director of DISCO in October of 1988.   Mr. OHeron is a 
graduate of the University of Dayton, and he served in the 
U.S. Army as an infantry platoon leader in Vietnam.
<br>
