<head>
<title>Deputy Director for Investigations</title>
<meta name="Author" content="William Howard">
<meta name="Project" content="home">
<meta name="Server" content="Internet">
<meta name="Date" content="10-15-96">
</head>

<body background="/images/texture.gif">
<h1><center>Deputy Director for Investigations</center>
<img src="/images/rharding.gif" align=bottom border=5> Rene' Davis-Harding</h1>
<hr>
<h2>Biography</h2>
<p>Ms. Davis-Harding was appointed Deputy Director for Investigations,
Defense Investigative Service on May 13, 1996.   She also serves as
the functional manager for the 1,200-person cadre of investigators
and polygraph examiners in the conduct of personnel security
investigations for the Department of Defense, elements of the
Intelligence Community, warfighting commands and other Federal
Government agencies.
<A HREF="people/rharding.htm">Complete Biography</A><br>
<br>
<hr>
<h2>The Office of the Director for Investigations</h2>
<p>Provides program management and supervision for Personnel Security Investigations (to include National Agency Checks), 
investigations of unauthorized disclosure of classified information, the DIS Polygraph Program, and other special investigations 
and surveys, as required. Develops policy, plans, procedures, and standards for the conduct of and training for, all 
investigative matters, and personally supervises highly sensitive investigations, as directed by the Director. Represents the 
Director in the coordination of investigations with the Military Department, Federal Bureau of Investigation, Office of the 
Secretary of Defense and other federal government agencies, and in forums and committees within the government. 
<hr>
<p><a href="invhome.htm"><img src="/images/back.gif" alt="back arrow" align=bottom border=0 width=40 height=40></a> Go back to the Investigations home page.
