<head>
<title>Personnel Investigations Center</title>
<meta name="Author" content="Matt Martelli">
<meta name="Project" content="home">
<meta name="Server" content="Internet">
<meta name="Date" content="8-22-96">
<link rel="next" href="invhome.htm">
</head>

<body background="/images/texture.gif">
<h1><center>Director for Personnel Investigations Center(PIC)</center></h1>
<h1><img src="/images/tstoltz.gif" align=bottom width=100 height=100> Anthony L. Stolz, Jr.</h1>
<hr>
<h2>Biography</h2>
<p>Anthony L. Stolz, Jr. (Tony), became the Director,
Personnel Investigations Center (PIC), Linthicum,
Maryland in January 1994. Prior to that, from
February 1990 to January 1994, he served as the DIS
Assistant Deputy Director, Investigative Policy at 
the Agency Headquarters.  Assignments earlier in his 
career included those of Special Agent, 
Special-Agent-In-Charge, Resident Agent, PIC Case 
Controller, PIC Team Chief, Assistant Chief, 
Investigations Division (PIC), Chief, Investigations 
Division (PIC), Headquarters Staff Officer, 
Instructor, and Deputy Director (PIC). Tony came 
from a U.S. Army background and is a Viet Nam 
veteran.  Assignments with the Army included stints 
with the 197th Infantry Brigade and the 10th Special 
Forces Group (Airborne).<br>
<hr>

<h2>The Office of the Director for Personnel Investigations Center</h2>

<p>Provides guidance, control, direction and management 
of the Investigations Center which controls and 
manages the 180,000 plus personnel security investigations 
initiated by DoD components annually.  The Center also maintains approximately 2.9 million 
closed investigations in it's mission as records 
repository for DoD clearance investigations.<br>
<hr>
