<head>
<title>EPSQ Updates Page</title>
<meta name="Author" content="William Howard">
<meta name="Project" content="EPSQ">
<meta name="Server" content="Internet">
<meta name="Date" content="8-13-96">
<link rel="previous" href="/projects/epsq/index.htm">
</head>

<body background="/images/texture.gif">
<p>&#160;<img src="/images/pccomp.gif" align=bottom width=88 height=63></p>
<H3>Hardware and Software Requirements for EPSQ</H3>
<p>Although EPSQ&#160;has been designed to operate on a wide variety of personal computers (PCs) and printers, the system 
requires certain minimum hardware and software components.</p>
<hr>
<h3>Hardware:</h3>
<ul>
<li>EPSQ&#160;requires the following minimum computer configuration: <ul>
<li>IBM-compatible personal computer (PC) with 80286 or greater CPU.</li>
<li>At least 640K&#160;of RAM with a minimum of 540K&#160;of contiguous conventional memory available.</li>
<li>6 Mb of free space on the hard disk for the Subject Edition; 12 Mb for the Security Officer Edition.</li>
<li>A floppy disk drive will be required to install EPSQ onto your system. The type of drive required will be 
determined by security officers when they make the installation diskettes.</li>
<li>Access to a printer. A list of printers supported by EPSQ&#160;is presented in Appendix B of the EPSQ&#160;Customer 
Manual.</li>
<li>For transmitting your data electronically to DIS, you will need either: a Hayes-compatible modem to 
communicate with our Value Added Network (VAN), or some type of connection to Internet.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3>Software:</h3>
<ul>
<li>EPSQ&#160;requires the following minimum software: <ul>
<li>Disk Operating System (DOS) version 3.3 or above.</li>
<li>Files=45 or greater in your CONFIG.SYS file.</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<br>
<P>
<p><a href="index.htm" target="body"><img src="/images/back.gif" alt="back arrow" align=bottom width=40 height=40></a> Go back to the EPSQ home page. 
