<html>

<head>
<title>Director for Investigations</title>
<meta name="Author" content="Matt Martelli">
<meta name="Project" content="home">
<meta name="Server" content="Internet">
<meta name="Date" content="9-12-96">
</head>

<body background="/images/texture.gif">
<br>
<center><IMG SRC="/images/ggwash.gif" ALT="[Picture]" WIDTH=100 HEIGHT=108 BORDER=5></center>
<br>
<center><H2>	GREGORY A. GWASH</h2>
<h3>	DEPUTY DIRECTOR FOR INDUSTRIAL SECURITY<br>
	DEFENSE INVESTIGATIVE SERVICE</h3></center>



<p>Greg Gwash, a native of Minnesota, has a bachelor's degree
in Russian Area Studies, a master's degree in Far Eastern
History and a juris doctorate degree.  He is currently
responsible for the implementation of the Defense portion
of the National Industrial Security Program (NISP) delegated
to the Defense Investigative Service (DIS), as well as the
Key Asset Protection Program, the Arms, Ammunition and
Explosives Program, and the DIS Counterintelligence
Integration Program.

<p>He is currently a member of the NISP Policy Advisory Committee
and was the Regulation Working Group Co-Chair of the NISP Task
Force.  Prior to his appointment in October l990 to the Senior
Executive Service as Deputy Director for Industrial Security,
DIS, he was Director of Industrial Security for the DIS Pacific
Region, located in Long Beach, California, where he was one of
the founders of the first Industrial Security Awareness Council.

<p>From l983 to l987, he was chief of DIS' Mannheim Germany Field
Office of Industrial Security - International, responsible for
security assistance to U.S. contractors and User Agencies in
Europe, the Middle East and Africa.

<p>Greg has served since l972 as an Industrial Security
Representative in Santa Barbara, Phoenix and Chicago.  

<p>Prior to his Federal civil service, Greg served in the United States
Army's Special Forces, including duty with the 5th Group in
Vietnam from l965 to l967.  

<p>He is also an inactive member of the California Bar Association.

<p><a href="../dind.htm"><img src="/images/back.gif" alt="back arrow" align=bottom border=0 width=40 height=40></a> Go back to the Industrial Security page.
<hr>
<address>Author: Matt Martelli<br>
Revised: 12 September 1996 </address>
</body>

