<h1>EPSQ Encryption Home Page! </h1>
<p><img src="/images/bar.gif" alt="------------------------------------------------------------------------------------" align=bottom width=641 height=6>
<h2>Current version of EPSQ </h2>
<p>The EPSQ system uses two levels of encryption: 
<p><img src="/images/ball_mag.gif" alt="*" align=bottom width=14 height=14><a href="encrdata.htm">Data entry</a> level.
<p><img src="/images/ball_mag.gif" alt="*" align=bottom width=14 height=14><a href="encrtran.htm">Transmission</a> level.
<hr>
<h2>Future levels of encryption </h2>
<p>With the release of a future version of EPSQ, either 2.0 or earlier, we plan on changing the encryption used. The following link will tell you more about the <a href="encrdiff.htm">differences</a> between current and future encryption methods used with EPSQ. 
<hr>
