<P>
 
Regional Seminar Update 

<P>
 
The National Counterintelligence Center (NACIC) and
the Emerald Coast Chapter of the National Classification Management
Society (NCMS) will sponsor a regional seminar on 21-22 March
1996, at Sandestin Inn, Destin, Florida. Mr. Raymond F. Humphrey-Vice
President, Digital Equipment Corporation-will deliver the keynote
address. Other speakers will be from NCMS Headquarters, the Federal
Bureau of Investigation, Defense Investigative Service, National
Security Agency, and the Information Security Oversight Office.
The point of contact for registration and other information is
Ms. Ruthie Kress, (904) 651-5559. Points of contact for the NACIC's
Community Training Branch are Supervisory Special Agent Cathy
Kiser, (703) 874-4078, and Mr. Steve Argubright, (703) 874-4073. 

<P>
 
The regional seminar series continues with a one-day
seminar at BDM Headquarters in Huntsville, Alabama, on Tuesday,
9 April 1996. Hosted by the Mid-south Chapter of NCMS and NACIC,
the keynote speaker will be Col. Frederick Dreisbach, USAF, Director,
Missile and Space Intelligence Center. Other speakers from the
US Government and the private sector will participate. The point
of contact for registration and other information is Ms. Sherry
Grasson, (205) 922-1941.  

<P>
 
Moving west to the ''Windy City,'' the Chicago Industrial
Security Advisory Council (ISAC) and the NACIC will host a regional
seminar on 19-20 June 1996. This seminar will be held at the Northrop
Grumman Corporation in Rolling Meadows, Illinois. Contact the
Community Training Branch for more information on this developing
seminar. 

<P>
 
The Gateway ISAC, the Heartland Chapter of NCMS,
and NACIC will sponsor a regional seminar at McDonnell Douglas
Headquarters in St. Louis, Missouri, on 21-22 August 1996. Contact
the Community Training Branch at (703) 874-4122 for more information
on the agenda and speakers scheduled to participate.  

<P>
 
For information on future seminars under consideration,
contact the Community Training Branch at (703) 874-4122. 

