Subject: Australian Fed Police LAC<BR>
<HR>
<P>
This file is an augmentation to ISL95L-2
<P>
<B>AUSTRALIAN FEDERAL POLICE</B>
<P>
The information in this form has been provided by
you to the Australian Federal Police for the purpose of obtaining
a criminal and/or traffic
records check, and you recognise that the result
will be taken into account in deciding whether to grant whatever
entitlement is sought.
<P>
<I>NOTE:</I>
<P>
The information obtained from you in this application
will not be used for any purpose other that indicated without
your prior consent except where
statutory obligations are placed on law enforcement
officials.<BR>

<P>
You may be requested to complete another consent
form in the future in relation to this or other entitlements and
any decision to comply shall be
of your own choosing.<BR>

<P>
As an alternative to completing this consent form
you may, if you wish, produce a certificate from the Police Force
in each State or Territory in
which you have lived during the past five years.
This would involve fingerprinting and payment of a fee.<BR>

<P>
Before completion of this form there are matters
that you should be aware of as follows<BR>

<P>
On 30 June 1990, new Commonwealth legislation came
into effect relating to the collection, use and disclosure of
old conviction information. The new
legislation is commonly known as the Spent Convictions
Scheme.<BR>

<P>
The aim of the Scheme is to prevent discrimination
on the basis of certain old convictions, once a waiting period
has passed and the individual has not

re-offended. The Scheme also covers situations where
an individual's conviction has been set aside or a pardon granted.
<BR>

<P>
An individual whose convictions is protection by
the provisions of the Spent Convictions Scheme does not have to
disclose that conviction to any person,
<P>
including a Commonwealth Authority, unless an exclusion
applies.<BR>

<P>
The Spent Conviction Scheme exclusionary provision
apply to many Commonwealth Authorities and advice thereon should
be sought before completion of this

form.<BR>
<BR>

<P>
I acknowledge that I have read these notes and am
aware of my entitlements:<BR>
<BR>

<P>
SIGNATURE:_________________________________ DATE:_____/______/______
<BR>
<BR>

<P>
[INSERT PAGE BREAK HERE]<BR>
<BR>

<P>
972B
<P>
CONSENT TO OBTAIN PERSONAL INFORMATION<BR>

<P>
I, ___________________________________________________________________
<BR>

<P>
CONSENT to the Australian Federal Police:<BR>


extracting from its own records; and
obtaining from another police force or other authority;
details of any criminal charge involving me pending before a court
together with details
of any conviction or finding of guilt which has been
recorded against me that is not covered by the provisions of an
exclusion; and
providing such information to: <BR>

<P>
<bllockquote>
The Regional Security Officer<br>
American Embassy<br>
Moonah Place<br>
Yarralumla A.C.T. 2600<BR>
</blockquote>
<P>
I ACKNOWLEDGE that any information provided may be
taken into account in relation to decisions concerning the grant
of an entitlement which in this
case is:

<P>
(SPECIFY)____________________________________________________________

<P>
I hereby certify that the personal details provided
on this form are true and correct.
<BR>
<br>
<P>
SIGNATURE:__________________________________ DATE:_____/______/______
<BR>
<BR>

<P>
<I>NOTE:</I><BR>

Provision of false or misleading information: 

<P>
In certifying that the personal particulars you have
provided are correct, you should be aware that the discovery that
you have provided false or
misleading information may lead to you being assessed
as not suitable for the grant of an entitlement as referred to
above. <BR>

<P>
This does not mean that the existence of a criminal
record will prevent the granting of an entitlement specified as
each case will be treated on its
merits. You should therefore supply truthful answers.
<BR>
<BR>

<P>
[INSERT PAGE BREAK HERE]<BR>
<BR>

<P>
792C
<P>
PERSONAL PARTICULARS FOR POLICE CHECK<BR>
<P>
FULL NAME:<BR>
(Miss/Mrs./Ms./Mr.) _____________________________________________________
<P>
(SURNAME) (Given Names) _____________________________________________________
<P>
PREVIOUS NAME: _____________________________________________________________________
<P>
