To: *interp.clarif<br>
From: lscheel<br>
Posted: Oct 5 09:08 1995 EDT (Oct 5 13:08 ZULU)<br>
Cc: <br>
Subject: Overseas Assignment for Consultants<BR>
<HR>
<P>
Paragraph 10-601c. Access to Classified Information
Overseas by Consultants:<BR>

<P>
We have been advised by the Office of the Assistant
Secretary of Defense (C3I) that the former policy on the use of
consultants in overseas areas still applies. That
is, consultants are eligible for access to classified information
outside the U.S. and its trust territories and possessions
provided overseas travel does not exceed 90 consecutive days
in any 12-month period.
<BR><BR>
</font>
